article.headline: San Diego 72, Fresno State 61
article.story: SAN DIEGO (AP) -- Nick Lewis scored 29 points to lead San Diego to a 72-61 victory over Fresno State Saturday in the first game of the San Diego Slam at Cox Arena. Washington State beat San Diego State 60-49 in the nightcap of the doubleheader. The win was the sixth in a row for the Toreros (7-2), while Fresno State dropped to 4-2. Lewis, who went 9-for-15 from the floor, scored his team's first 10 points in the second half as San Diego boosted its 39-34 halftime lead to 54-46. Fresno State pulled within three points at 54-51 with just over six minutes to play but Lewis and Corey Belser sparked a 14-5 run to finish off the Bulldogs. Belser had 14 points and 10 rebounds. Lewis had eight rebounds and was 9-for-11 from the free-throw line. Quinton Hosley led Fresno State with 18 points, Dwight O'Neil had 13 and Hector Hernandez 12. San Diego was 17-for-23 from the free-throw line, Fresno State 17-for-32.
